  <h5 class="card-title">Academic Criteria:</h5>
  <p class="card-text">The candidates who are willing to join the TVS should  fulfill the academic criteria given below:
 
<br>•	A minimum of 60 % in graduation.
<br>•	B.E/B. Tech, B.Com, B.Sc, M. Tech, M.E, M.Com, M.Sc etc., can now apply for TVS Off-Campus.
<br>•	The gap between their academic years should not be more than 2 years.
<br>•	The candidates of all the above-mentioned categories are eligible for this drive.
 
<h5 class="card-title">Backlog Criteria:</h5>
<br>The student who wants to apply for TVS should not have any kind of backlogs. In the case of, backlogs the student’s profile will be rejected.
  
    
  <h5 class="card-title">SELECTION PROCESS</h5>
    <p class="card-text">Following are the steps in the Selection Process in case of TVS Recruitment:
<br>•	Online Test
<br>•	Technical Interview
<br>•	HR Round
<p class="card-text">Online round test comprises of two sections : Aptitude Test and Technical Test.</p>
<p class="card-text">The first round i.e. the Online test or sometimes taken in offline mode; consists of an Aptitude Test comprising of the following sub-heads:
</p>
<br>•	Quantitative Aptitude
<br>•	Verbal Ability
<br>•	Logical Reasoning
 
<p class="card-text">Second round  i.e. the Technical Interview part comprises of a test comprising of  questions focussing mainly on the kind of profile applied by the canditates.
 
 </p>
 
 
<p class="card-text">Third round as a part of the recruitment process comprises of HR questions that are mainly focussed on Resume , internships carried by the canditates and other questions as to how the canditate is an asset for the company , why he should be hired , what are the qualities that differentiate him/her from other canditates.
 
<br>*To test and evaluate your skills and embrace your knowledge you can take up a free mock test on TVS.To prcatice more kindly purchase from various subscription options available on menturrbuddy.
    
 

    <h4 class="card-title">PATTERN</h4>
    <p class="card-text">Following is the Pattern undertaken by TVS in the selection process:
 
<br>Paper sections	Number of Questions	Time duration
<br>Aptitude	30	40 mins
<br>Technical	70	80 mins
<br>Total	100	120 mins
 
<br>* There is no negative marking.
<br>The total time allotted to answer the 100 questions is 120 minutes.
 
 
<p class="card-text">Following are some highlighted points which should be kept in mind in the above mentioned exams regard:
<br>-The written exam contains both Technical and General Ability Questions (Aptitude, General Knowledge, and Reasoning).
<br>-The number of questions in technical section varies from 70-80 depending upon the exam paper designed and the profile offered to the canditates.
      <br> -50 and above  is the sectional  cut off. However it may vary according to the paper designed and the number of canditates applying for the post.
      <br> -In exceptional situations company does have  negative marking as well.
       <br>- The level of paper difficulty is equivalent to GATE exam.</p>
 
    
    

